==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stria
<hw>Stri"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Striae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a furrow, channel,
hollow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A minute groove, or channel; a
threadlike line, as of color; a narrow structural band or line; a
striation; <as>as, the <ex>striae</ex>, or groovings, produced on a rock
by a glacier passing over it; the <ex>striae</ex> on the surface of a
shell; a <ex>stria</ex> of nervous matter in the brain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A fillet between the flutes of
columns, pilasters, or the like.</def> <rj><au>Oxf. Gloss.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Striate</ent>⟦br⟧
